{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2640,"text":"Whoa, dude."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6520,"text":"Check out those killer equations. Sweet."},{"time":12240,"text":"Actually, for the next 18 minutes\nI'm going to do the best I can"},{"time":15680,"text":"to describe the beauty\nof particle physics without equations."},{"time":19640,"text":"It turns out there's a lot\nwe can learn from coral."},{"time":23120,"text":"A coral is a very beautiful\nand unusual animal."},{"time":25840,"text":"Each coral head consists\nof thousands of individual polyps."},{"time":29400,"text":"These polyps are continually\nbudding and branching"},{"time":31960,"text":"into genetically identical neighbors."},{"time":34800,"text":"If we imagine this\nto be a hyperintelligent coral,"},{"time":37880,"text":"we can single out an individual\nand ask him a reasonable question."},{"time":41080,"text":"We can ask how exactly\nhe got to be in this particular location"},{"time":44480,"text":"compared to his neighbors --"},{"time":46200,"text":"if it was just chance,\nor destiny, or what?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49720,"text":"Now, after admonishing us\nfor turning the temperature up too high,"},{"time":54000,"text":"he would tell us that our question\nwas completely stupid."},{"time":56840,"text":"These corals can be kind of mean, you see,"},{"time":58864,"text":"and I have surfing scars to prove that."},{"time":61503,"text":"But this polyp would continue and tell us"},{"time":63480,"text":"that his neighbors were\nquite clearly identical copies of him."},{"time":66560,"text":"That he was in all\nthese other locations as well,"},{"time":68920,"text":"but experiencing them\nas separate individuals."},{"time":72280,"text":"For a coral, branching\ninto different copies"},{"time":74640,"text":"is the most natural thing in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77320,"text":"Unlike us, a hyperintelligent coral"},{"time":79720,"text":"would be uniquely prepared\nto understand quantum mechanics."},{"time":83840,"text":"The mathematics of quantum mechanics"},{"time":85600,"text":"very accurately describes\nhow our universe works."},{"time":88160,"text":"And it tells us our reality is continually\nbranching into different possibilities,"},{"time":92042,"text":"just like a coral."},{"time":94480,"text":"It's a weird thing for us humans\nto wrap our minds around,"},{"time":97240,"text":"since we only ever get\nto experience one possibility."},{"time":100120,"text":"This quantum weirdness was first described"},{"time":102144,"text":"by Erwin Schrödinger and his cat."},{"time":103920,"text":"The cat likes this version better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109440,"text":"In this setup, Schrödinger is in a box\nwith a radioactive sample"},{"time":113120,"text":"that, by the laws of quantum mechanics,\nbranches into a state"},{"time":116040,"text":"in which it is radiated\nand a state in which it is not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123640,"text":"In the branch in which\nthe sample radiates,"},{"time":125680,"text":"it sets off a trigger that releases poison\nand Schrödinger is dead."},{"time":129080,"text":"But in the other branch of reality,\nhe remains alive."},{"time":132000,"text":"These realities are experienced\nseparately by each individual."},{"time":134929,"text":"As far as either can tell,\nthe other one doesn't exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137880,"text":"This seems weird to us,"},{"time":139120,"text":"because each of us\nonly experiences an individual existence,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and we don't get to see other branches."},{"time":144120,"text":"It's as if each of us,\nlike Schrödinger here,"},{"time":146440,"text":"are a kind of coral\nbranching into different possibilities."},{"time":150880,"text":"The mathematics\nof quantum mechanics tells us"},{"time":153040,"text":"this is how the world\nworks at tiny scales."},{"time":155360,"text":"It can be summed up in a single sentence:"},{"time":158320,"text":"Everything that can happen, does."},{"time":160360,"text":"That's quantum mechanics."},{"time":161840,"text":"But this does not mean everything happens."},{"time":164600,"text":"The rest of physics is about describing\nwhat can happen and what can't."},{"time":168960,"text":"What physics tells us\nis that everything comes down to geometry"},{"time":172120,"text":"and the interactions\nof elementary particles."},{"time":174840,"text":"And things can happen only if\nthese interactions are perfectly balanced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180600,"text":"Now I'll go ahead and describe\nhow we know about these particles,"},{"time":183680,"text":"what they are and how this balance works."},{"time":187120,"text":"In this machine,\na beam of protons and antiprotons"},{"time":190080,"text":"are accelerated to near the speed of light"},{"time":192120,"text":"and brought together in a collision,\nproducing a burst of pure energy."},{"time":195800,"text":"This energy is immediately converted\ninto a spray of subatomic particles,"},{"time":199720,"text":"with detectors and computers\nused to figure out their properties."},{"time":203040,"text":"This enormous machine --"},{"time":204320,"text":"the Large Hadron Collider\nat CERN in Geneva --"},{"time":206520,"text":"has a circumference of 17 miles\nand, when it's operating,"},{"time":209240,"text":"draws five times as much power\nas the city of Monterey."},{"time":212840,"text":"We can't predict specifically"},{"time":214720,"text":"what particles will be produced\nin any individual collision."},{"time":217680,"text":"Quantum mechanics tells us\nall possibilities are realized."},{"time":221080,"text":"But physics does tell us\nwhat particles can be produced."},{"time":224520,"text":"These particles must have\njust as much mass and energy"},{"time":227080,"text":"as is carried in\nby the proton and antiproton."},{"time":230560,"text":"Any particles more massive\nthan this energy limit aren't produced,"},{"time":233840,"text":"and remain invisible to us."},{"time":236840,"text":"This is why this new\nparticle accelerator is so exciting."},{"time":239920,"text":"It's going to push\nthis energy limit seven times"},{"time":242200,"text":"beyond what's ever been done before,"},{"time":243960,"text":"so we're going to get to see\nsome new particles very soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247360,"text":"But before talking\nabout what we might see,"},{"time":249520,"text":"let me describe the particles\nwe already know of."},{"time":252400,"text":"There's a whole zoo\nof subatomic particles."},{"time":255200,"text":"Most of us are familiar with electrons."},{"time":257120,"text":"A lot of people in this room\nmake a good living pushing them around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261560,"text":"But the electron also has\na neutral partner called the neutrino,"},{"time":264600,"text":"with no electric charge\nand a very tiny mass."},{"time":267400,"text":"In contrast, the up and down quarks\nhave very large masses,"},{"time":270880,"text":"and combine in threes to make\nthe protons and neutrons inside atoms."},{"time":274760,"text":"All of these matter particles\ncome in left- and right-handed varieties,"},{"time":278120,"text":"and have antiparticle partners\nthat carry opposite charges."},{"time":282360,"text":"These familiar particles"},{"time":283640,"text":"also have less familiar\nsecond and third generations,"},{"time":286680,"text":"which have the same charges as the first\nbut have much higher masses."},{"time":291680,"text":"These matter particles all interact\nwith the various force particles."},{"time":295240,"text":"The electromagnetic force\ninteracts with electrically charged matter"},{"time":298480,"text":"via particles called photons."},{"time":300320,"text":"There is also a very weak force"},{"time":301880,"text":"called, rather unimaginatively,\nthe weak force ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304637,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305800,"text":"that interacts\nonly with left-handed matter."},{"time":308440,"text":"The strong force acts between quarks"},{"time":310480,"text":"which carry a different kind of charge,\ncalled color charge,"},{"time":313640,"text":"and come in three different varieties:\nred, green and blue."},{"time":316440,"text":"You can blame Murray Gell-Mann\nfor these names -- they're his fault."},{"time":320160,"text":"Finally, there's the force of gravity,"},{"time":322280,"text":"which interacts with matter\nvia its mass and spin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325400,"text":"The most important thing\nto understand here"},{"time":327640,"text":"is that there's a different kind of charge\nassociated with each of these forces."},{"time":332000,"text":"These four different forces\ninteract with matter"},{"time":334280,"text":"according to the corresponding charges\nthat each particle has."},{"time":338640,"text":"A particle that hasn't been seen yet,\nbut we're pretty sure exists,"},{"time":341840,"text":"is the Higgs particle, which gives masses\nto all these other particles."},{"time":345560,"text":"The main purpose\nof the Large Hadron Collider"},{"time":347720,"text":"is to see this Higgs particle,\nand we're almost certain it will."},{"time":351120,"text":"But the greatest mystery\nis what else we might see."},{"time":355160,"text":"And I'm going to show you\none beautiful possibility"},{"time":357600,"text":"towards the end of this talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360200,"text":"Now, if we count up\nall these different particles"},{"time":362560,"text":"using their various spins and charges,"},{"time":364440,"text":"there are 226."},{"time":366400,"text":"That's a lot of particles\nto keep track of."},{"time":368880,"text":"And it seems strange"},{"time":370120,"text":"that nature would have\nso many elementary particles."},{"time":373680,"text":"But if we plot them out\naccording to their charges,"},{"time":376360,"text":"some beautiful patterns emerge."},{"time":380120,"text":"The most familiar charge\nis electric charge."},{"time":382840,"text":"Electrons have an electric charge,"},{"time":384520,"text":"a negative one,"},{"time":385760,"text":"and quarks have\nelectric charges in thirds."},{"time":387800,"text":"So when two up quarks and a down quark\nare combined to make a proton,"},{"time":391080,"text":"it has a total\nelectric charge of plus one."},{"time":393120,"text":"These particles also have antiparticles,\nwhich have opposite charges."},{"time":396400,"text":"Now, it turns out the electric charge"},{"time":398240,"text":"is actually a combination\nof two other charges:"},{"time":400760,"text":"hypercharge and weak charge."},{"time":403440,"text":"If we spread out\nthe hypercharge and weak charge"},{"time":406762,"text":"and plot the charges of particles\nin this two-dimensional charge space,"},{"time":410120,"text":"the electric charge\nis where these particles sit"},{"time":412400,"text":"along the vertical direction."},{"time":414440,"text":"The electromagnetic\nand weak forces interact with matter"},{"time":417120,"text":"according to their hypercharge\nand weak charge,"},{"time":419360,"text":"which make this pattern."},{"time":420640,"text":"This is called\nthe unified electroweak model,"},{"time":422800,"text":"and it was put together back in 1967."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425720,"text":"The reason most of us\nare only familiar with electric charge"},{"time":428600,"text":"and not both of these\nis because of the Higgs particle."},{"time":432400,"text":"The Higgs, over here on the left,\nhas a large mass"},{"time":435160,"text":"and breaks the symmetry\nof this electroweak pattern."},{"time":437640,"text":"It makes the weak force very weak\nby giving the weak particles a large mass."},{"time":441240,"text":"Since this massive Higgs sits along\nthe horizontal direction in this diagram,"},{"time":445360,"text":"the photons of electromagnetism\nremain massless"},{"time":447680,"text":"and interact with electric charge\nalong the vertical direction"},{"time":450640,"text":"in this charge space."},{"time":453960,"text":"So the electromagnetic and weak forces"},{"time":455840,"text":"are described by this pattern\nof particle charges"},{"time":458200,"text":"in two-dimensional space."},{"time":459600,"text":"We can include the strong force\nby spreading out its two charge directions"},{"time":464600,"text":"and plotting the charges\nof the force particles in quarks"},{"time":467320,"text":"along these directions."},{"time":469240,"text":"The charges of all known particles"},{"time":470920,"text":"can be plotted in\na four-dimensional charge space,"},{"time":473320,"text":"and projected down to two dimensions\nlike this so we can see them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476520,"text":"Whenever particles interact,\nnature keeps things in a perfect balance"},{"time":480320,"text":"along all four of these charge directions."},{"time":483120,"text":"If a particle and an antiparticle collide,"},{"time":485200,"text":"it creates a burst of energy\nand a total charge of zero"},{"time":487880,"text":"in all four charge directions."},{"time":489920,"text":"At this point, anything can be created"},{"time":491960,"text":"as long as it has the same energy\nand maintains a total charge of zero."},{"time":496160,"text":"For example, this weak force particle\nand its antiparticle"},{"time":499400,"text":"can be created in a collision."},{"time":501200,"text":"In further interactions,\nthe charges must always balance."},{"time":504120,"text":"One of the weak particles could decay\ninto an electron and an antineutrino,"},{"time":509160,"text":"and these three\nstill add to zero total charge."},{"time":511840,"text":"Nature always keeps a perfect balance."},{"time":514799,"text":"So these patterns of charges\nare not just pretty."},{"time":517760,"text":"They tell us what interactions\nare allowed to happen."},{"time":520280,"text":"And we can rotate this charge space\nin four dimensions"},{"time":522919,"text":"to get a better look\nat the strong interaction,"},{"time":525720,"text":"which has this nice hexagonal symmetry."},{"time":528000,"text":"In a strong interaction,\na strong force particle,"},{"time":531360,"text":"such as this one,"},{"time":532600,"text":"interacts with a colored quark,\nsuch as this green one,"},{"time":536160,"text":"to give a quark with a different\ncolor charge -- this red one."},{"time":540160,"text":"And strong interactions\nare happening millions of times"},{"time":542800,"text":"each second in every atom of our bodies,"},{"time":544960,"text":"holding the atomic nuclei together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"But these four charges\ncorresponding to three forces"},{"time":551880,"text":"are not the end of the story."},{"time":553920,"text":"We can also include two more charges\ncorresponding to the gravitational force."},{"time":557880,"text":"When we include these,"},{"time":559200,"text":"each matter particle\nhas two different spin charges,"},{"time":561880,"text":"spin-up and spin-down."},{"time":563880,"text":"So they all split and give a nice pattern\nin six-dimensional charge space."},{"time":567960,"text":"We can rotate this pattern\nin six dimensions"},{"time":570960,"text":"and see that it's quite pretty."},{"time":575200,"text":"Right now, this pattern\nmatches our best current knowledge"},{"time":578760,"text":"of how nature is built at the tiny scales\nof these elementary particles."},{"time":583040,"text":"This is what we know for certain."},{"time":584680,"text":"Some of these particles\nare at the very limit"},{"time":586840,"text":"of what we've been able to reach\nwith experiments."},{"time":589240,"text":"From this pattern"},{"time":590480,"text":"we already know the particle physics\nof these tiny scales --"},{"time":593840,"text":"the way the universe works\nat these tiny scales is very beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599120,"text":"But now I'm going to discuss\nsome new and old ideas"},{"time":601560,"text":"about things we don't know yet."},{"time":603680,"text":"We want to expand this pattern\nusing mathematics alone,"},{"time":606840,"text":"and see if we can get our hands\non the whole enchilada."},{"time":609480,"text":"We want to find\nall the particles and forces"},{"time":611600,"text":"that make a complete picture\nof our universe."},{"time":613760,"text":"And we want to use this picture\nto predict new particles"},{"time":616440,"text":"that we'll see when experiments\nreach higher energies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620920,"text":"So there's an old idea in particle physics"},{"time":623200,"text":"that this known pattern of charges,"},{"time":625960,"text":"which is not very symmetric,"},{"time":627560,"text":"could emerge from a more perfect pattern\nthat gets broken --"},{"time":630440,"text":"similar to how the Higgs particle\nbreaks the electroweak pattern"},{"time":633480,"text":"to give electromagnetism."},{"time":635160,"text":"In order to do this,\nwe need to introduce new forces"},{"time":638240,"text":"with new charge directions."},{"time":641480,"text":"When we introduce a new direction,"},{"time":643200,"text":"we get to guess what charges\nthe particles have along this direction,"},{"time":646640,"text":"and then we can rotate it\nin with the others."},{"time":649720,"text":"If we guess wisely,\nwe can construct the standard charges"},{"time":653240,"text":"in six charge dimensions\nas a broken symmetry"},{"time":655960,"text":"of this more perfect pattern\nin seven charge dimensions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660040,"text":"This particular choice\ncorresponds to a grand unified theory"},{"time":663040,"text":"introduced by Pati and Salam in 1973."},{"time":666440,"text":"When we look at this new unified pattern,"},{"time":669200,"text":"we can see a couple of gaps\nwhere particles seem to be missing."},{"time":673080,"text":"This is the way\ntheories of unification work."},{"time":675960,"text":"A physicist looks for larger,\nmore symmetric patterns"},{"time":678520,"text":"that include the established\npattern as a subset."},{"time":681680,"text":"The larger pattern allows us\nto predict the existence of particles"},{"time":684840,"text":"that have never been seen."},{"time":687240,"text":"This unification model\npredicts the existence"},{"time":689520,"text":"of these two new force particles,"},{"time":692040,"text":"which should act a lot\nlike the weak force, only weaker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696160,"text":"Now, we can rotate this set\nof charges in seven dimensions"},{"time":698920,"text":"and consider an odd fact\nabout the matter particles:"},{"time":702600,"text":"the second and third generations of matter"},{"time":704680,"text":"have exactly the same charges\nin six-dimensional charge space"},{"time":707600,"text":"as the first generation."},{"time":709480,"text":"These particles are not\nuniquely identified by their six charges."},{"time":713320,"text":"They sit on top of one another\nin the standard charge space."},{"time":717400,"text":"However, if we work\nin eight-dimensional charge space,"},{"time":721040,"text":"then we can assign\nunique new charges to each particle."},{"time":725360,"text":"Then we can spin these in eight dimensions"},{"time":728440,"text":"and see what the whole pattern looks like."},{"time":731983,"text":"Here we can see the second\nand third generations of matter now,"},{"time":734960,"text":"related to the first generation\nby a symmetry called \"triality.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":739520,"text":"This particular pattern\nof charges in eight dimensions"},{"time":743040,"text":"is actually part of the most beautiful\ngeometric structure in mathematics."},{"time":747760,"text":"It's a pattern of the largest\nexceptional Lie group, E8."},{"time":751720,"text":"This Lie group is a smooth,\ncurved shape with 248 dimensions."},{"time":755760,"text":"Each point in this pattern\ncorresponds to a symmetry"},{"time":758760,"text":"of this very complex and beautiful shape."},{"time":761760,"text":"One small part of this E8 shape\ncan be used to describe"},{"time":764560,"text":"the curved space-time\nof Einstein's general relativity,"},{"time":767200,"text":"explaining gravity."},{"time":769200,"text":"Together with quantum mechanics,"},{"time":770920,"text":"the geometry of this shape\ncould describe everything"},{"time":773400,"text":"about how the universe works\nat the tiniest scales."},{"time":776040,"text":"The pattern of this shape living\nin eight-dimensional charge space"},{"time":780360,"text":"is exquisitely beautiful,"},{"time":783040,"text":"and it summarizes thousands\nof possible interactions"},{"time":785520,"text":"between these elementary particles,"},{"time":787240,"text":"each of which is just a facet\nof this complicated shape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791480,"text":"As we spin it, we can see\nmany of the other intricate patterns"},{"time":794440,"text":"contained in this one."},{"time":797480,"text":"And with a particular rotation,"},{"time":799280,"text":"we can look down through this pattern\nin eight dimensions along a symmetry axis"},{"time":803480,"text":"and see all the particles at once."},{"time":805320,"text":"It's a very beautiful object,"},{"time":806920,"text":"and as with any unification,"},{"time":809320,"text":"we can see some holes where new particles\nare required by this pattern."},{"time":813840,"text":"There are 20 gaps\nwhere new particles should be,"},{"time":816600,"text":"two of which have been filled\nby the Pati-Salam particles."},{"time":819360,"text":"From their location in this pattern,\nwe know that these new particles"},{"time":822640,"text":"should be scalar fields\nlike the Higgs particle,"},{"time":825000,"text":"but have color charge\nand interact with the strong force."},{"time":828240,"text":"Filling in these new particles\ncompletes this pattern,"},{"time":830800,"text":"giving us the full E8."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832160,"text":"This E8 pattern has\nvery deep mathematical roots."},{"time":835200,"text":"It's considered by many to be the most\nbeautiful structure in mathematics."},{"time":839280,"text":"It's a fantastic prospect that this object\nof great mathematical beauty"},{"time":843440,"text":"could describe the truth\nof particle interactions"},{"time":845800,"text":"at the smallest scales imaginable."},{"time":849720,"text":"And this idea that nature is described\nby mathematics is not at all new."},{"time":853680,"text":"In 1623, Galileo wrote this:"},{"time":857360,"text":"\"Nature's grand book,\nwhich stands continually open to our gaze,"},{"time":861080,"text":"is written in the language of mathematics."},{"time":863600,"text":"Its characters are triangles,\ncircles and other geometrical figures,"},{"time":867240,"text":"without which it is humanly impossible\nto understand a single word of it;"},{"time":871120,"text":"without these, one is wandering around\nin a dark labyrinth.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":875560,"text":"I believe this to be true,"},{"time":877440,"text":"and I've tried\nto follow Galileo's guidance"},{"time":879480,"text":"in describing the mathematics\nof particle physics"},{"time":881840,"text":"using only triangles, circles\nand other geometrical figures."},{"time":885240,"text":"Of course, when other physicists\nand I actually work on this stuff,"},{"time":889000,"text":"the mathematics\ncan resemble a dark labyrinth."},{"time":892920,"text":"But it's reassuring that at the heart\nof this mathematics"},{"time":895800,"text":"is pure, beautiful geometry."},{"time":899440,"text":"Joined with quantum mechanics,"},{"time":900920,"text":"this mathematics describes our universe\nas a growing E8 coral,"},{"time":904880,"text":"with particles interacting\nat every location in all possible ways"},{"time":908520,"text":"according to a beautiful pattern."},{"time":911560,"text":"And as more of the pattern\ncomes into view using new machines"},{"time":914480,"text":"like the Large Hadron Collider,"},{"time":916320,"text":"we may be able to see whether nature\nuses this E8 pattern or a different one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921760,"text":"This process of discovery is\na wonderful adventure to be involved in."},{"time":925680,"text":"If the LHC finds particles\nthat fit this E8 pattern,"},{"time":929000,"text":"that will be very, very cool."},{"time":931960,"text":"If the LHC finds new particles,\nbut they don't fit this pattern --"},{"time":935120,"text":"well, that will be very interesting,\nbut bad for this E8 theory."},{"time":939640,"text":"And, of course, bad for me personally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":944360,"text":"Now, how bad would that be?"},{"time":946160,"text":"Well, pretty bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":951400,"text":"But predicting how nature works\nis a very risky game."},{"time":955200,"text":"This theory and others like it\nare long shots."},{"time":959080,"text":"One does a lot of hard work\nknowing that most of these ideas"},{"time":961960,"text":"probably won't end up\nbeing true about nature."},{"time":964160,"text":"That's what doing\ntheoretical physics is like:"},{"time":966360,"text":"there are a lot of wipeouts."},{"time":967800,"text":"In this regard, new physics theories\nare a lot like start-up companies."},{"time":973360,"text":"As with any large investment,"},{"time":974800,"text":"it can be emotionally difficult\nto abandon a line of research"},{"time":977720,"text":"when it isn't working out."},{"time":979040,"text":"But in science,\nif something isn't working,"},{"time":981120,"text":"you have to toss it out\nand try something else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984160,"text":"Now, the only way to maintain sanity"},{"time":985920,"text":"and achieve happiness\nin the midst of this uncertainty"},{"time":988560,"text":"is to keep balance\nand perspective in life."},{"time":992440,"text":"I've tried the best I can\nto live a balanced life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":997560,"text":"I try to balance my life equally\nbetween physics, love and surfing --"},{"time":1001160,"text":"my own three charge directions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005160,"text":"This way, even if the physics\nI work on comes to nothing,"},{"time":1007880,"text":"I still know I've lived a good life."},{"time":1010240,"text":"And I try to live in beautiful places."},{"time":1012160,"text":"For most of the past ten years\nI've lived on the island of Maui,"},{"time":1015240,"text":"a very beautiful place."},{"time":1016840,"text":"Now, it's one of the greatest mysteries\nin the universe to my parents"},{"time":1020560,"text":"how I managed to survive all that time"},{"time":1022440,"text":"without engaging in anything\nresembling full-time employment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025359,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028960,"text":"I'm going to let you in on that secret."},{"time":1032359,"text":"This was a view\nfrom my home office on Maui."},{"time":1036560,"text":"And this is another,"},{"time":1039720,"text":"and another."},{"time":1041160,"text":"And you may have noticed\nthat these beautiful views are similar,"},{"time":1044200,"text":"but in slightly different places."},{"time":1046640,"text":"That's because this used to be\nmy home and office on Maui."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051880,"text":"I've chosen a very unusual life."},{"time":1054720,"text":"But not worrying about rent"},{"time":1056080,"text":"allowed me to spend my time\ndoing what I love."},{"time":1058960,"text":"Living a nomadic existence\nhas been hard at times,"},{"time":1061520,"text":"but it's allowed me\nto live in beautiful places"},{"time":1063760,"text":"and keep a balance in my life\nthat I've been happy with."},{"time":1066760,"text":"It allows me to spend a lot of my time\nhanging out with hyperintelligent coral."},{"time":1072880,"text":"But I also greatly enjoy\nthe company of hyperintelligent people."},{"time":1076040,"text":"So I'm very happy\nto have been invited here to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079320,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087200,"text":"Chris Anderson: Stay here one second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089010,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1092616,"text":"I probably understood two percent of that,"},{"time":1094640,"text":"but I still absolutely loved it."},{"time":1098240,"text":"So I'm going to sound dumb."},{"time":1099880,"text":"Your theory of everything --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102240,"text":"Garrett Lisi: I'm used to coral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103840,"text":"CA: That's right."},{"time":1105120,"text":"The reason it's got\na few people at least excited"},{"time":1107480,"text":"is because, if you're right, it brings\ngravity and quantum theory together."},{"time":1111880,"text":"So are you saying that we should\nthink of the universe, at its heart --"},{"time":1115720,"text":"that the smallest things that there are,"},{"time":1118440,"text":"are somehow an E8 object of possibility?"},{"time":1124640,"text":"I mean, is there a scale to it,\nat the smallest scale, or ...?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127680,"text":"GL: Well, right now\nthe pattern I showed you"},{"time":1130560,"text":"that corresponds to what we know\nabout elementary particle physics --"},{"time":1135200,"text":"that already corresponds\nto a very beautiful shape."},{"time":1137640,"text":"And that's the one\nthat I said we knew for certain."},{"time":1140080,"text":"And that shape\nhas remarkable similarities --"},{"time":1143200,"text":"and the way it fits into this E8 pattern,\nwhich could be the rest of the picture."},{"time":1148120,"text":"And these patterns of points\nthat I've shown for you"},{"time":1151600,"text":"actually represent symmetries\nof this high-dimensional object"},{"time":1155440,"text":"that would be warping\nand moving and dancing"},{"time":1158240,"text":"over the space-time that we experience."},{"time":1160360,"text":"And that would be what explains all these\nelementary particles that we see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1164040,"text":"CA: But a string theorist,\nas I understand it,"},{"time":1167440,"text":"explains electrons in terms\nof much smaller strings vibrating --"},{"time":1170480,"text":"I know, you don't like string theory --\nvibrating inside it."},{"time":1173800,"text":"How should we think\nof an electron in relation to E8?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178640,"text":"GL: Well, it would be one\nof the symmetries of this E8 shape."},{"time":1182800,"text":"So what's happening is, as the shape\nis moving over space-time, it's twisting."},{"time":1188200,"text":"And the direction it's twisting\nas it moves is what particle we see."},{"time":1192680,"text":"So it would be --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193920,"text":"CA: The size of the E8 shape,\nhow does that relate to the electron?"},{"time":1197120,"text":"I feel like I need that for my picture.\nIs it bigger? Is it smaller?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200360,"text":"GL: As far as we know,\nelectrons are point particles,"},{"time":1202861,"text":"so this would be going down\nto the smallest possible scales."},{"time":1205720,"text":"So the way these things are explained\nin quantum field theory is,"},{"time":1209560,"text":"all possibilities are expanding\nand developing at once."},{"time":1212240,"text":"And this is why\nI use the analogy to coral."},{"time":1215200,"text":"And --"},{"time":1217600,"text":"in this way, the way that E8 comes in"},{"time":1221920,"text":"is it will be as a shape that's attached\nat each point in the space-time."},{"time":1227280,"text":"And, as I said,\nthe way the shape twists --"},{"time":1230760,"text":"the directional along which way\nthe shape is twisting"},{"time":1233280,"text":"as it moves over this curved surface --"},{"time":1235360,"text":"is what the elementary particles\nare, themselves."},{"time":1238160,"text":"So through quantum field theory,"},{"time":1240840,"text":"they manifest themselves as points\nand interact that way."},{"time":1244080,"text":"I don't know if I'll be able\nto make this any clearer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1246640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1249600,"text":"CA: It doesn't really matter."},{"time":1251040,"text":"It's evoking a kind of sense of wonder,"},{"time":1253080,"text":"and I certainly\nwant to understand more of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257880,"text":"But thank you so much for coming.\nThat was absolutely fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1261040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}